---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
// DRAFT: Omer, confirm the Re_Tera one-liner + facts + link below. Do not present unverified
// specifics as fact. Everything here is drafted from what is public at getretera.com.
const url = 'https://getretera.com';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Re_Tera · Omer Bese"
  description="Re_Tera: a home inventory app that gets you ready for the insurance claim you hope you never file."
  path="/retera"
>
  <div class="phead">
    <div class="eyebrow">retera</div>
    <h1>The claim you hope you never file, prepared before you need it.</h1>
    <p class="sub">Re_Tera is a home inventory app: scan your rooms, catalog what you own, and keep the documentation an insurer actually asks for.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="body">
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Almost nobody has a real inventory of what they own, and everybody discovers this at
        the worst possible moment, standing in front of an adjuster after a fire, a flood, or a
        break-in, trying to remember what was in the room. Re_Tera exists to make that moment
        boring.
      </p>
      <p>
        You walk your home, capture your rooms and your belongings, and Re_Tera keeps the
        catalog and the paper trail current, so the documentation is already done when you need
        it. It is the same instinct as the rest of my work: do the unglamorous preparation once,
        so the expensive surprise later is just a formality.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href={url}>See Re_Tera <span>&#8599;</span></a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
<style>
  .body{padding:clamp(36px,5vw,56px) var(--gutter)}
  .body .prose{max-width:var(--measure)}
</style>
